column5: We got spoiled last year.

Here is a report.  Knee is doing better. It’s been 3 weeks since surgery. I still sleep with the brace but can walk around the house without it. Physio says i’m Doing well and to keep at it. This is taking longer then I thought. Work is a pain in the butt to do with a sore leg and I’m angry about not being able to eat while driving due to the new laws.

Been getting out since Dec 1st.  5 lakes so far.  Just don't like using photobucket, so I really don't post pics anymore.  Stupid website gave me a virus a few years back...
5 lakes.  Damn. Lol
I can't wait for simcoe to freeze over, I hope to do more ice fishing this year.
5 weeks into the season now, ice and snow is set up nicely in the north.  Had mainly beautiful conditions thus far but it seems like some real winter conditions are knocking on the door.
Check out imgur. Simple and easy to use.
Photobucket charges fees now if you want to post photos to other sites.  Flickr is still free though and there are other sites too.

Some of the Kawarthas are OK. Just the dead end bays where there is no current. Huts out on Chemong at Rotary Park today. I was out on a different east Kawartha lake yesterday. 6 inches there.
